import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the correlation between u and v?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist2d(data['u'], data['v'], bins=30, cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.colorbar().set_label('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the joint distribution of u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    mean_u = np.mean(data['u'])
    std_u = np.std(data['u'])
    mean_v = np.mean(data['v'])
    std_v = np.std(data['v'])
    
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'], label='Data points')
    plt.axvline(mean_u, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean u: {mean_u:.2f}')
    plt.axhline(mean_v, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean v: {mean_v:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the mean and standard deviation of u and v?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
